Prorogation of Parliament August 1940 Memorandum in connection with prorogation which was expected to take place in August 1940 This file contains a record of the letters sent out in connection with Prorogation of the first Session of the Nineteenth Parliament. However, the Prime Minister introduced a resolution in the house to the effect that Parliament would adjourn until 5 November 1940, and that there would be no Prorogation. F.L.C.P.
